            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">M1913.00.00</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Thomas Hall to AAAS</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Published report: AAAS Congress, 1913, Melbourne. <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">p/c at MEL</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Standard"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">I can't find this in the volume </seg>
                     <ref target="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/15368068"
                          rend="Internet%20link"
                          style="color: #0000ff; ">
                        <seg style="color: #0000ff; ">
                           <hi rend="underline">https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/15368068</hi>
                        </seg>
                     </ref>
                  </p>
                  <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
               </note>THE SCIENCE CONGRESS</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">A SUMMARY</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">By: T. S. Hall.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">[Included in summary of Australasian Association for the Advancement of Science:]</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="Footnote"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The writer well remembers a stirring speech made by the late Baron von Mueller to the Field Naturalists' Club when preparations were being made for the first visit of the association to Melbourne in 1890. In his curious German-English he told us how he, when a young man, had attended a similar German association; and then there rolled forth the names of the great men whom he had seen and talked to for the first time, Helmholtz, the physicist, and Johannes Mueller, the <seg style="background-color: #ffff00; ">anatonomist</seg>, and many another; and then he told us of the inspiration which he derived from the meeting. It is in this actual meeting that, to my mind, the great value of the sessions lies, and I for one must plead guilty for having often played truant from sectional meetings to enjoy a quiet smoke and chat in the grounds. […]</p>
